{"title_page": "2016 Canadian Mixed Curling Championship", "text_new": "{{infobox curling\n| Name = 2016 Canadian Mixed Curling Championship\n| Logo = \n| Size = \n| Host city = [[Toronto]], [[Ontario]]\n| Arena = [[Weston Golf & Country Club]]\n| Dates = November 8\u201315, 2015\n| Winner = '''{{AB}}'''\n| Curling club = [[Saville Sports Centre|Saville SC]], [[Edmonton]]\n| Skip = [[Mick Lizmore]] \n| Third = [[Sarah Wilkes]] \n| Second = [[Brad Thiessen (curler)|Brad Thiessen]] \n| Lead = [[Alison Kotylak]]\n| Finalist = {{SK}} ([[Bruce Korte]])\n| prev = [[2015 Canadian Mixed Curling Championship|2015]]\n| next = [[2017 Canadian Mixed Curling Championship|2017]]\n}}\nThe '''2016 [[Canadian Mixed Curling Championship]]''' was held from November 7 to 14, 2015 at the [[Weston Golf & Country Club]] in [[Toronto]], [[Ontario]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.curling.ca/2016mixed/2014/03/11/weston-club-in-toronto-host-2016-canadian-mixed/|title=Weston Club in Toronto host 2016 Canadian Mixed|date=11 March 2015|publisher=[[Canadian Curling Association]]|accessdate=23 June 2015}}</ref> The winning Alberta team represented Canada at the [[2016 World Mixed Curling Championship]].\n\nAlberta won its 11th Canadian Mixed Championship.<ref>https://www.curling.ca/files/2019/11/2020-Mixed-Guide-Formatted.pdf</ref>\n\n==Teams==\nThe teams are listed as follows:<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.curling.ca/2016mixed/category/teams/|title=2016 Canadian Mixed Curling Championship \u2013 Teams|publisher=[[Canadian Curling Association]]|accessdate=23 June 2015}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Team !! Skip !! Third !! Second !! Lead !! Locale\n|-\n| {{AB}} || [[Mick Lizmore]] || [[Sarah Wilkes]] || [[Brad Thiessen (curler)|Brad Thiessen]] || [[Alison Kotylak]] || [[Saville Sports Centre|Saville SC]], [[Edmonton]]\n|-\n| {{BC}} || [[Dean Joanisse]] || [[Shannon Aleksic]] || [[Tyler Orme]] || [[Kelsey Steiger]] || [[Royal City Curling Club|Royal City CC]], [[New Westminster]]\n|-\n| {{M