nadian Mixed|date=11 March 2015|publisher=[[Canadian Curling Association]]|accessdate=23 June 2015}}</ref> The winning Alberta team represented Canada at the [[2016 World Mixed Curling Championship]].\n\nAlberta won its 11th Canadian Mixed Championship.<ref>https://www.curling.ca/files/2019/11/2020-Mixed-Guide-Formatted.pdf</ref>\n\n==Teams==\nThe teams are listed as follows:<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.curling.ca/2016mixed/category/teams/|title=2016 Canadian Mixed Curling Championship \u2013 Teams|publisher=[[Canadian Curling Association]]|accessdate=23 June 2015}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Team !! Skip !! Third !! Second !! Lead !! Locale\n|-\n| {{AB}} || [[Mick Lizmore]] || [[Sarah Wilkes]] || [[Brad Thiessen (curler)|Brad Thiessen]] || [[Alison Kotylak]] || [[Saville Sports Centre|Saville SC]], [[Edmonton]]\n|-\n| {{BC}} || [[Dean Joanisse]] || [[Shannon Aleksic]] || [[Tyler Orme]] || [[Kelsey Steiger]] || [[Royal City Curling Club|Royal City CC]], [[New Westminster]]\n|-\n| {{MB}} || [[Bob Sigurdson]] || [[Erika Sigurdson]] || [[Al Purdy (curler)|Al Purdy]] || [[Lindsay Baldock]] || [[Granite Curling Club (Winnipeg)|Granite CC]], [[Winnipeg]]\n|-\n| {{NB}} || [[Charlie Sullivan (curler)|Charlie Sullivan]] || [[Leah Thompson (curler)|Leah Thompson]] || [[Paul Nason]] || [[Joanne Freeze]] || [[Thistle St. Andrews Curling Club|Thistle St. Andrews CC]], [[Saint John, New Brunswick|Saint John]]\n|-\n| {{NL}} || [[Chris Ford (curler)|Chris Ford]] || [[Marie Christianson]] || [[Cory Ewart]] || [[Lauren Wasylkiw]] || [[RE/MAX Centre]], [[St. John's, Newfoundland and Labrador|St. John's]]\n|-\n| {{NO}} || [[Colin Koivula]] || [[Oye-Sem Won Briand]] || [[Chris Briand]] || [[Amanda Gates]] || [[Port Arthur Curling Club|Port Arthur CC]], [[Thunder Bay]]\n|-\n| {{NT}} || [[Steve Moss (curler)|Steve Moss]] || [[Dawn Moses]] || [[Brett Zubot]] || [[Debbie Moss]] || [[Yellowknife Curling Centre|Yellowknife CC]], [[Yellowknife]]\n|-\n| {{NS}} || [[Doug MacKenzie (c