 Nadu|Seventh Assembly]]||27 June 1980 || 18 August 1983 ||  Leader of the Opposition (2)<ref name=\"assembly\"/>||37/112<ref>[[#seventh|Statistical report on Tamil Nadu Assembly general elections 1980]], p. 10</ref>\n|- style=\"background:#cfc;\"\n| [[Ninth Assembly of Tamil Nadu|Ninth Assembly]]||27 January 1989 || 30 January 1991|| Chief Minister (3)<ref name=\"assembly\"/>||150/202<ref>[[#ninth|Statistical report on Tamil Nadu Assembly general elections 1989]], p. 10</ref>\n|- style=\"background:#cfc;\"\n| [[Tenth Assembly of Tamil Nadu|Tenth Assembly]]||26 April 1991|| 30 March 1996||Member of Legislative Assembly<ref name=\"assembly\"/>|| 2/176<ref>[[#ninth|Statistical report on Tamil Nadu Assembly general elections 1991]], p. 10</ref>\n|- style=\"background:#ffc;\"\n| [[Eleventh Assembly of Tamil Nadu|Eleventh Assembly]] || 13 May 1996 || 14 May 2001|| Chief Minister (4)<ref name=\"assembly\"/>||173/182<ref>[[#eleventh|Statistical report on Tamil Nadu Assembly general elections 1996]], p. 11</ref>\n|- style=\"background:#cfc;\"\n| [[Thirteenth Assembly of Tamil Nadu|Thirteenth Assembly]] || 13 May 2006 || 14 May 2011|| Chief Minister (5)<ref name=\"assembly\"/>||96/132<ref>[[#stat2006|Statistical report on Tamil Nadu Assembly general elections 2006]], p. 11</ref>\n|- style=\"background:#ffc;\"\n| [[Fourteenth Assembly of Tamil Nadu|Fourteenth Assembly]] || 16 May 2011 || 19 May 2016|| Member of Legislative Assembly ||23/124\n|- style=\"background:#ffc;\"\n| [[Fifteenth Assembly of Tamil Nadu|Fifteenth Assembly]] || 19 May 2016 || 7 August 2018 (died)|| Member of Legislative Assembly ||89/176\n|}\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of political families]]\n*[[Karunanidhi family]]\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n==References==\n* {{cite book\n  | last = Guneratne\n  | ref = Guneratne\n  | first = Anthony R.\n  |author2=Wimal Dissanayake |author3=Sumita S. Chakravarty\n   | title = Rethinking Third Cinema\n  | publisher = Routledge\n  | year = 2003\n  | url = ht